result.execSummary:
The defendant Denise M Browning was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
9:28 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Lisa Vanden Branden for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement - upon plea to count 2, will recommend probation and count 1 will be dismissed and read-in.  State concurs.  Defendant concurs - will accept offer.  Court goes over right to counsel.  Defendant waives right to counsel.  Court accepts waiver.

Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty and as domestic.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty to count 2 as charged.  Court orders count 1 be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  ADA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by ADA.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

30 days county jail, stayed and places the defendant on probation for 12 months.  Court grants huber if probation becomes revoked.

CONDITIONS:

-Court costs.
-Domestic Abuse Assessment
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent.

Court orders the $150 cash bond on file be applied to the costs.

Court adjourned at 9:35 a.m.

9:22 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Lisa Vanden Branden for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by defendant - will not be getting an attorney and will be meeting with the DA tomorrow.  Court sets for Status Hearing on December 15, 2015 at 9:15 a.m.

Court adjourned at 9:23 a.m.

9:32 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Lisa Vanden Branden for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by defendant - will not be getting an attorney.  Court goes over right to counsel.  Defendant waives right to counsel.  Court accepts waiver.  Court sets for Status Hearing on December 1, 2015 at 9:15 a.m.  Defendant to make appointment with the DA's office.

Court adjourned at 9:34 a.m.

9:07 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading.  Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Court instructs the defendant of his right to an attorney.  Defendant enters a plea of NOT GUILTY.  DA makes bond recommendation - requests cash bond to continue.  Court notes $150 cash bond on file and orders bond to continue with condition of:  No violent contact with Gerald B.  Court will set for Status Hearing on November 17, 2015 at 9:15 a.m.
